    LEADER BOARD TOURNAMENT DISK..LOADING INSTRUCTIONS:
    
    (1)  The security key from your original LEADER BOARD game must be
    plugged into the rear joystick port (port #2) for the TOURNAMET DISK to
    work properly.
    
    (2) Plug the mouse into the front port (port #1)
    
    (3) Insert your kickstart disk.
    (4) When the workbench disk is requested, insert the LEADER BOARD
    TOURNAMENT DISK into drive 0
    
    .NOTES:
    (1) Amiga LEADER BOARD requires version 1.1 kickstart.
    (2) LEADER BOARD TOUNAMENT DISK requires a full 512K of memory.  The
    program will not work if the operating system has allocated a
    significant amount of memory to another device or program.
    (3) LEADER BOARD TOURNAMENT DISK must reside in the first 512K of
    memory.  Memory expansion devices can cause the program to fail.
    (4) If you have a 5 1/4" drive connected to your system, it must be
    turned on..
